FLEXUSNET WEBSITE VERSION 2.2 - CHANGE LOG (UPDATED)
================================================================================
Date: Current session
Purpose: Document all changes made to enable future rollback/undo operations

================================================================================
SUMMARY OF CHANGES
================================================================================

1. Moved "100% Nationwide Service Coverage" badge to right side of carousel
2. Made badge static (removed animation)
3. Made badge smaller (reduced text and icon sizes)
4. Aligned badge with header email/phone position
5. Positioned badge with negative margins for precise right alignment
6. Fixed text visibility in service cards (Network Installations and POS Systems)
7. Removed header transparency (made header fully opaque)

================================================================================
FILE CHANGES
================================================================================

1. components/HeroCarousel.tsx
   - MODIFIED: Nationwide Coverage Badge positioning
   - Changed from centered (top center) to right-aligned
   - Removed animate-float class (made static)
   - Reduced sizes: text from text-xl md:text-2xl to text-lg md:text-xl
   - Reduced icon size: from w-8 h-8 to w-6 h-6
   - Reduced padding: from px-8 py-4 to px-6 py-3
   - Reduced spacing: from space-x-3 to space-x-2
   - Positioned using max-w-7xl container to align with header
   - Used negative margins (-mr-8 sm:-mr-10 lg:-mr-16) for right alignment

2. components/ServiceRequestForm.tsx
   - MODIFIED: Service card text visibility
   - Changed "Network Installations" subtitle from text-gray-300 to text-gray-600
   - Changed "POS Systems" subtitle from text-gray-300 to text-gray-600
   - All three service cards now use text-gray-600 for consistent visibility
   - This ensures all service card descriptions are equally readable

3. components/Header.tsx
   - MODIFIED: Header background transparency
   - Changed from bg-white/95 backdrop-blur-md to bg-white
   - Removed transparency (was 95% opaque, now 100% opaque)
   - Header is now fully opaque when scrolling, preventing content bleed-through
   - This fixes logo background visibility issues when scrolling

